A farmhand linked to the murder of Kakamega DC Paul Yatich's wife has been detained for 14 days. Boniface Kiptoo was on Monday arraigned before Chief Magistrate Charles Obulutsa in Eldoret. This followed his arrest in Nakuru on Saturday, October 27. DCI officer John Wanyonyi told the court that the suspect was found with items believed to be from Loise' house. "We believe he has useful information concerning the killing since he was an employee of the deceased and went missing after the incident." He was found with Loise's driving licence, Equity Bank ATM card, and Boresha Sacco ATM card. Obulutsa allowed the police to hold the suspect for 14 days in order to complete the investigations into the murder of Loyce Yatich. The case will be mentioned on November 12. The late was a TSC employee in charge of curriculum development in Uasin Gishu. Loise' decomposing body was found at her house in Kiplombe, Eldoret two weeks ago. She had deep cuts all over her body. Police suspect she was raped before being killed. Two suspects Laban Cheruiyot and Simon Lumile were arrested at Kabiyet market in Nandi last week while driving a vehicle belonging to the slain TSC employee. The suspects were produced also before Obulutsa and were also detained 14 days for policeÂ to complete investigations. Separately, a court has ordered that Loise's burial dispute be heard as from Tuesday. Eldoret principal magistrate Naomi Wairimu issued temporary orders restraining Yatich from taking the body for burial. Sophie Yegon, a sister of the deceased, obtained court orders on behalf of the family members stopping the same. Click here for the latest political news